	<article class="post-248317 post type-post status-publish hentry tag-environmental-protection-agency tag-greenhouse-gas-emissions tag-obama-barack tag-united-states-politics-and-government per-obama-barack des-greenhouse-gas-emissions des-united-states-politics-and-government org-environmental-protection-agency" id="post-248317">
	<header class="postHeader">
				<div class="postKicker">
					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Reaction to Obama Administration Carbon Emissions Proposal</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By The New York Times			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-06-02T15:06:28+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">June 2, 2014 11:06 am</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">June 2, 2014 11:06 am</span>		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Advocates and critics respond<a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/06/03/us/politics/obama-epa-rule-coal-carbon-pollution-power-plants.html"> to the news that President Obama will bypass Congress</a> and take one of the biggest steps any American president has ever taken on climate change.<br />
<span id="more-248317"></span>
<div id="liveUpdatesModule" class="liveUpdatesModule">
<div class="type-live-update update">
<div id="senate-republicans-ready-to-fight-e-p-a-rules" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#senate-republicans-ready-to-fight-e-p-a-rules">3:19 P.M.</a></span> <strong>Senate Republicans Ready to Fight E.P.A. Rules</strong></h5>
</p></div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Critics are calling President Obama&#8217;s climate plan the &#8220;war on coal,&#8221; and for states that rely heavily on coal for electricity curbing emissions could be costly. Here&#8217;s a roundup of reaction from (mostly Republican) Senators in those states:</p>
