<div id="e-p-a-makes-case-for-change" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#e-p-a-makes-case-for-change">11:05 A.M.</a></span> <strong>E.P.A. Makes Case for Change</strong></h5>
</p></div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The Environmental Protection Agency&#8217;s administrator, Gina McCarthy, made a robust case for acting on climate change. Here are some central quotes from her speech:</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢âClimate change fueled by pollution is supercharging risk.â<br />
â¢âFor the sake of our families&#8217; health and for our kids&#8217; future, we have a moral obligation to act on climate.â<br />
â¢âWeâll turn risks on climate into business opportunity.â<br />
â¢âIâm a little tired of people pointing to the polar vortex as a reason not to act on climate. Itâs the exact opposite. Itâs a wake-up call.&#8221;<br />
â¢âOver four decades, E.P.A. has cut air pollution by 70 percent and the economy has more than tripled. Climate action doesnât actually dull Americaâs competitive edge, it sharpens it.â<br />
â¢âThe most costly thing we can do is to do nothing.â</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8212; <em>ALAN RAPPEPORT</em></p>
</div></div>
<div class="type-live-update update">
<div id="a-white-board-explainer-video-from-the-e-p-a" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#a-white-board-explainer-video-from-the-e-p-a">10:40 A.M.</a></span> <strong>A &#8220;White Board&#8221; Explainer Video From the E.P.A.</strong></h5>
</p></div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><iframe width="480" height="270" src="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AcNTGX_d8mY?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">As part of its &#8220;White Board&#8221; series, the E.P.A. has published a video on YouTube explaining the proposed regulations. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Standing before a mural drawn in marker of coal plants, percentages and pie charts, Joe Goffman, an E.P.A. official, offered a brief argument for the new regulations &#8212; &#8220;Global climate change could threaten our very way of life&#8221; &#8212; while going through the rules step by step.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8212; <em>NICK CORASANITI</em></p>
</div></div>
<div class="type-live-update update">
<div id="e-p-a-says-plan-will-slow-climate-change-create-jobs" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#e-p-a-says-plan-will-slow-climate-change-create-jobs">10:09 A.M.</a></span> <strong>E.P.A. Says Plan Will Slow Climate Change, Create Jobs</strong></h5>
</p></div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The Environmental Protection Agency is out with a preview of its Clean Power Plan proposal, and it makes the case that the regulations will create jobs and spur innovation. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Gina McCarthy, the E.P.A. administrator, <a href="//yosemite.epa.gov/opa/admpress.nsf/bd4379a92ceceeac8525735900400c27/5bb6d20668b9a18485257ceb00490c98!OpenDocument">said in a statement</a>, &#8220;We don&#8217;t have to choose between a healthy economy and a healthy environment &#8212; our action will sharpen Americaâs competitive edge, spur innovation, and create jobs.&#8221; </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">According to the E.P.A., the proposal will not only reduce carbon emissions form the power sector by 30 percent, but also avoid up to 6,600 premature deaths and provide up to $93 billion in climate and public health benefits. It also claims that the policy will shrink electricity bills by 8 percent by increasing energy efficiency and reducing demand.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8212; <em>ALAN RAPPEPORT</em></p>
</div></div>
</div>
	</div>
		<footer class="entry-footer">
